<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900411-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>900411-0026.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Fuji Heavy Industries   Says Nissan Executive   Is Elected President</HL><DATE>04/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   WNEWS J.FJH NSANY</CO><LP>   TOKYO -- Fuji Heavy Industries Ltd. said it will replaceits president with an executive from Nissan Motor Co.,fueling speculation that the larger company will exert morecontrol over financially strapped Fuji.   Fuji, which makes cars under the name Subaru, saidToshihiro Tajima, the 70-year-old president, &quot;would releasehimself from the duty of president&quot; following the shareholderannual meeting June 28. He will remain as chairman.</LP><TEXT>   The company said the new president will be Isamu Kawai,67, currently president of Nissan Diesel Motor Co. Nissanholds 4.4% of Fuji, making Nissan Fuji's largest shareholder.   Last month, Fuji said it would post a loss of 23 billionyen ($145.6 million) in the year ended March 31, sharplyhigher than the early projected loss of three billion yen.It's the company's first loss since its shares were listed onthe Tokyo Stock Exchange in 1960.   After yesterday's announcement, Nissan President YutakaKume said that &quot;as far as Nissan is concerned, if we wereasked to give Fuji Heavy Industries support and assistance,we are willing to proceed in that direction on the basis ofdiscussions once the new organization is in place.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>